message.content:
cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network backbone discovery and proposes a graph theoretical and information theoretical model for it.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper deals with discovering the underlying networking structure of complex systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the central role of a backbone in carrying out system functionality and traffic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes an efficient mining algorithm based on Kullback-Leibler divergence optimization procedure and maximal weight connected subgraph discovery procedure.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper proposes an information theoretical model for network backbone discovery.
